fixes #941

This splits the Bamboo build script for linux into two:

- One builds in debug mode with coverage enabled and does not produce eggs or wheels. The coverage info will be extracted from this job.
- One builds in release mode with coverage disabled and produces binary and source distributions. The release artifacts will be extracted from this job.

* Added method `frame.copy()`;
* Several modes of Frame initialization are now done in C++ instead of in Python;
* Creating a Frame from `core._DataTable` object is no longer supported (the use of these objects will be slowly phased out).

WIP for #1066

* Old idiom was:
  function()
  {
    if (retVal) {
      return nSize;
    }else{
      return $something;
    }
    return -1;
  }

  Transformed to:

  function()
  {
    if (retVal)
      return nSize;

    //rest
  }

